article.headline: Brown 62, Dartmouth 50
article.story: HANOVER, N.H. -- Rafael Maia matched his season high with 21 points on 10-of-11 shooting from the field as Brown cruised past Dartmouth 62-50 Friday night in Ivy League action. The Bears (8-9, 2-1), coming off a 76-64 overtime loss to Navy that snapped a three-game winning streak, never trailed and led by as many as 14 in the first half. Brown took its biggest lead at 48-29 with 12:34 left on Stephen Albrechts' 3-pointer. Sean McGonagill added 12 points and Tucker Halpern 10 for the Bears, while leading scorer Matt Sullivan scored only five points, about 10 fewer than his average. Brown outshot the Big Green from the field 52.2 percent (24 of 46) to 43.5 percent (20 of 46). The Bears outscored Dartmouth 28-14 in the paint and had a 27-23 rebounding advantage. Connor Boehm scored 16 to lead Dartmouth (4-13, 0-3), which has lost three of its past four games.
